This paper discusses the optimization of deep neural networks for mobile inference, which is a topic that falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the impact of CPU resource contention on latency variability, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of DNN models on different devices, which falls under the category of architecture (cs.AR).
